1
00:00:14,395 --> 00:00:19,833
<i>Connecting old words</i>
<i>that have been used up</i>

2
00:00:20,668 --> 00:00:28,575
<i>I just want to convey</i>
<i>my simple thoughts</i>

3
00:00:28,643 --> 00:00:34,013
<i>That day's faint wind blows away</i>

4
00:00:34,081 --> 00:00:38,142
<i>at the castle ruins of yesterday</i>

5
00:00:39,387 --> 00:00:44,290
<i>I'll laugh with you</i>
<i>and live for the moment</i>

6
00:00:45,026 --> 00:00:51,932
<i>Still that incident</i>
<i>will continue to trouble you, right?</i>

7
00:00:53,334 --> 00:00:56,826
<i>That's why it must be good bye</i>

8
00:00:56,904 --> 00:01:03,810
<i>Leaving nothing behind,</i>
<i>let us share what is left</i>

9
00:01:03,945 --> 00:01:11,010
<i>In time, we'll realize</i>
<i>that it was everything</i>

10
00:01:11,085 --> 00:01:17,752
<i>And sadness will touch our cheeks,</i>
<i>creating a river of tears</i>

11
00:01:18,159 --> 00:01:27,727
<i>Trembling thoughts swept into a vortex</i>
<i>and melting away</i>

12
00:01:42,427 --> 00:01:44,418
I'll let you out of here.

13
00:01:45,197 --> 00:01:48,564
And I'll grant you one wish, too.

14
00:01:49,101 --> 00:01:50,568
You don't have to worry.

15
00:01:50,635 --> 00:01:55,834
Your strong will is going to remain
as Residual Aura inside me.

16
00:01:56,875 --> 00:01:59,571
It's not like you'll lose everything.

17
00:02:03,181 --> 00:02:06,776
Now then, your flesh is mine.

18
00:02:13,892 --> 00:02:16,986
<i>With this, Lord Orochimaru's body</i>
<i>has once again</i>

19
00:02:17,062 --> 00:02:19,553
<i>become unable to reanimate</i>
<i>for several years.</i>

20
00:02:20,198 --> 00:02:21,893
<i>However there's a next time...</i>

21
00:02:25,537 --> 00:02:31,874
I-Indeed. My body no longer has value
as a vessel for Reanimation Jutsu.

22
00:02:33,245 --> 00:02:36,442
It will now be difficult for me
who has lost everything...

23
00:02:36,515 --> 00:02:40,076
to find my own calling

24
00:02:41,153 --> 00:02:44,020
I've finally understood that.

25
00:02:46,758 --> 00:02:49,192
Even if it's not me...

26
00:02:49,261 --> 00:02:54,597
I'll bring in the new "vessel,"
even if it costs me my life.

27
00:02:55,500 --> 00:02:59,027
That's my repayment to
Lord Orochimaru.

28
00:03:00,472 --> 00:03:05,705
That's the only redemption for me...
who was worthless.

29
00:03:06,778 --> 00:03:11,738
<i>Miscalculation. A New Enemy Appears!</i>

30
00:03:24,229 --> 00:03:25,093
They're fast.

31
00:03:33,939 --> 00:03:34,871
Akamaru.

32
00:03:35,407 --> 00:03:37,375
Come quick after you've set the bombs!

33
00:03:48,353 --> 00:03:49,320
Oh no!

34
00:03:54,526 --> 00:03:55,288
All right.

35
00:03:55,460 --> 00:03:56,290
Great.

36
00:03:56,695 --> 00:03:58,287
Akamaru, well done.

37
00:04:16,114 --> 00:04:17,979
Messing with me.

38
00:04:19,918 --> 00:04:20,577
Akamaru.

39
00:04:21,219 --> 00:04:23,210
Don't you "arf" me, you mutt!

40
00:04:27,092 --> 00:04:28,491
I'll waste you.

41
00:04:34,666 --> 00:04:35,530
Hold on.

42
00:04:35,800 --> 00:04:37,392
You!

43
00:04:50,515 --> 00:04:53,006
Kiba! Akamaru!

44
00:04:53,485 --> 00:04:54,747
Damn it.

45
00:05:20,378 --> 00:05:22,107
What's happening?

46
00:05:24,416 --> 00:05:25,815
You punks!

47
00:05:26,518 --> 00:05:28,315
Where are Kiba and Akamaru?!

48
00:05:28,420 --> 00:05:30,149
Another one's come.

49
00:05:32,223 --> 00:05:33,349
We have no choice.

50
00:05:33,458 --> 00:05:37,792
I'll take care of this, so you take
the coffin and go on ahead.

51
00:05:38,229 --> 00:05:38,991
Shikamaru...

52
00:05:39,064 --> 00:05:39,928
Get going already.

53
00:05:48,173 --> 00:05:50,505
Wh-Why are you...?

54
00:06:24,876 --> 00:06:28,869
I'm sorry, Naruto.
It's my miscalculation.

55
00:06:30,849 --> 00:06:32,282
Kimimaro.

56
00:06:41,393 --> 00:06:44,328
You were taking too long, Tayuya.

57
00:06:47,732 --> 00:06:50,997
And what happened to
the other three?

58
00:06:52,237 --> 00:06:54,831
Being none other than those
of the former "Sound Ninja Five."

59
00:06:57,642 --> 00:06:59,303
Why are you...?

60
00:07:00,211 --> 00:07:03,840
Your body... Your body's no longer...

61
00:07:05,450 --> 00:07:11,650
I'm not moving with the flesh anymore.
It's mental power.

62
00:07:13,691 --> 00:07:15,682
Man, you cheater of death...

63
00:07:16,428 --> 00:07:19,659
I understand a little now,
that feeling...

64
00:07:19,731 --> 00:07:25,033
of being information that has escaped
from the prison of the flesh.

65
00:07:31,609 --> 00:07:35,602
The feeling of experiencing
a taste of Lord Orochimaru's dream.

66
00:07:37,015 --> 00:07:38,448
Orochimaru...!

67
00:07:39,451 --> 00:07:43,080
This vessel... is an important vessel
for the dream...

68
00:07:43,988 --> 00:07:47,389
The flesh that Lord Orochimaru
truly desires.

69
00:07:48,092 --> 00:07:50,686
But you guys were a bit too late.

70
00:07:55,400 --> 00:07:58,062
<i>Some dangerous guy</i>
<i>has appeared again.</i>

71
00:07:58,470 --> 00:08:01,166
<i>That air about him is</i>
<i>nothing ordinary.</i>

72
00:08:02,173 --> 00:08:05,404
<i>Anyway, we need</i>
<i>to sort out the situation.</i>

73
00:08:05,577 --> 00:08:07,204
<i>If we were to carelessly</i>
<i>plunge in...</i>

74
00:08:07,278 --> 00:08:11,772
You jerk.
What're you babbling nonsense?

75
00:08:11,850 --> 00:08:12,578
Naruto!

76
00:08:12,650 --> 00:08:14,242
Give back Sasuke!

77
00:08:14,519 --> 00:08:15,543
Hey, wait!

78
00:08:34,472 --> 00:08:35,166
Tayuya.

79
00:08:36,441 --> 00:08:39,899
The reason why I won't kill you now

80
00:08:39,978 --> 00:08:44,506
is because you have a mission
you have to complete.

81
00:08:45,850 --> 00:08:51,220
And <i>my</i> mission is to deliver
that to Lord Orochimaru.

82
00:08:51,689 --> 00:08:53,680
Isn't it too late now?

83
00:08:54,492 --> 00:08:56,983
Humph. I told you.

84
00:08:57,362 --> 00:09:01,321
That's the body that Lord Orochimaru
truly desires.

85
00:09:01,966 --> 00:09:03,866
The next vessel, huh?

86
00:09:05,770 --> 00:09:07,203
That's right...

87
00:09:07,839 --> 00:09:11,297
And this is the only thing that
I can do at present.

88
00:09:12,744 --> 00:09:16,475
I leave those two pieces
of garbage to you.

89
00:09:22,720 --> 00:09:23,948
Sasuke...

90
00:09:24,522 --> 00:09:26,149
That punk!

91
00:09:26,224 --> 00:09:27,418
Calm down, Naruto.

92
00:09:27,592 --> 00:09:28,991
How can I calm down?

93
00:09:29,327 --> 00:09:32,228
At this rate,
Sasuke will get far away again.

94
00:09:35,934 --> 00:09:37,697
<i>Naruto's right.</i>

95
00:09:38,102 --> 00:09:40,866
<i>This is a mission to bring Sasuke back</i>
<i>to the Leaf Village.</i>

96
00:09:41,439 --> 00:09:44,897
<i>We must choose what would be</i>
<i>the most rational means</i>

97
00:09:44,976 --> 00:09:46,375
<i>to execute the mission.</i>

98
00:10:04,963 --> 00:10:06,123
Damned punks.

99
00:10:06,197 --> 00:10:07,755
I'll finish this in a flash.

100
00:10:09,434 --> 00:10:10,867
Naruto, listen up.

101
00:10:11,836 --> 00:10:15,067
Please move according to the plan
that I'm going to tell you.

102
00:10:23,315 --> 00:10:26,079
<i>He's a classic close range</i>
<i>combat type fool</i>

103
00:10:26,151 --> 00:10:28,415
<i>with Shadow Clone Jutsu</i>
<i>as his only saving grace.</i>

104
00:10:29,087 --> 00:10:31,112
<i>And he's a middle range</i>
<i>combat type</i>

105
00:10:31,189 --> 00:10:34,522
<i>who binds his enemies with</i>
<i>a Jutsu using shadows...</i>

106
00:10:34,592 --> 00:10:37,220
<i>and a sharp squad leader, huh?</i>

107
00:10:41,099 --> 00:10:42,259
Got it?

108
00:10:42,334 --> 00:10:43,062
Yeah.

109
00:10:44,602 --> 00:10:46,433
Come on already, you punks.

110
00:10:48,707 --> 00:10:51,039
It's two versus one.
We've got the upper hand.

111
00:10:51,343 --> 00:10:53,538
It's an opponent we can beat
if we team up.

112
00:10:53,678 --> 00:10:54,804
Let's go, Naruto.

113
00:10:54,879 --> 00:10:55,868
All right.

114
00:10:56,981 --> 00:10:58,778
With garbage like you jerks,

115
00:10:58,850 --> 00:11:00,909
it doesn't matter how many
of you are there.

116
00:11:01,286 --> 00:11:03,686
Don't underestimate our teamwork.

117
00:11:03,755 --> 00:11:04,881
Let's go!

118
00:11:09,394 --> 00:11:10,452
Bring it.

119
00:11:12,897 --> 00:11:14,057
Now... Naruto.

120
00:11:15,066 --> 00:11:16,761
I'll blow you away.

121
00:11:24,008 --> 00:11:26,533
Gotcha. The strategy is a success.

122
00:11:27,112 --> 00:11:28,704
Farewell.

123
00:11:34,452 --> 00:11:35,350
Blast.

124
00:11:35,420 --> 00:11:36,819
You tricked me.

125
00:11:36,921 --> 00:11:40,254
Teamwork, my foot. You little punks...

126
00:11:47,399 --> 00:11:48,559
Blast.

127
00:11:52,237 --> 00:11:55,934
You wouldn't fall for the same trick
over and over, huh?

128
00:11:56,408 --> 00:11:59,377
Small fry... You've got nerve.

129
00:12:00,512 --> 00:12:04,505
Well, I guess I'll settle for just
having been able to let him get away.

130
00:12:05,216 --> 00:12:06,740
Remember this.

131
00:12:06,818 --> 00:12:09,548
It's not just Jutsu that are weapons.

132
00:12:13,224 --> 00:12:15,488
<i>I'm counting on you, Shikamaru.</i>

133
00:12:23,234 --> 00:12:25,862
<i>Hang in there, Sasuke.</i>

134
00:12:34,946 --> 00:12:36,607
But that kid,

135
00:12:36,681 --> 00:12:39,809
how wonderful it is that
he can move with that body, eh?

136
00:12:39,884 --> 00:12:45,220
Kabuto, I don't know what kind
of order you gave him,

137
00:12:45,290 --> 00:12:47,053
but it's a bit harsh.

138
00:12:48,092 --> 00:12:50,890
Not at all.
It wasn't an order.

139
00:12:51,496 --> 00:12:55,227
I don't like to force things.

140
00:12:56,100 --> 00:12:58,364
He acted on his own.

141
00:13:00,538 --> 00:13:03,564
For you whom he reveres.

142
00:13:05,543 --> 00:13:10,606
Kabuto... You've really got
a hateful personality, don't you?

143
00:13:10,982 --> 00:13:12,347
Lord Orochimaru.

144
00:13:13,117 --> 00:13:17,520
To you,
Kimimaro was a perfect existence...

145
00:13:18,289 --> 00:13:22,055
His thoughts were steeped in darkness
in the same way as yours.

146
00:13:22,160 --> 00:13:24,151
And he sanctified you.

147
00:13:24,596 --> 00:13:27,394
And he fanatically admired
and revered you.

148
00:13:29,367 --> 00:13:34,600
Moreover, he was of the Shinobi clan
with the strongest and perfect bodies

149
00:13:34,672 --> 00:13:40,770
being the legitimate bloodline
of their Kekkai Genkai...

150
00:13:40,845 --> 00:13:42,608
until a short time ago.

151
00:13:43,681 --> 00:13:44,545
Yes...

152
00:13:45,416 --> 00:13:49,750
When I think about having lost him,
I still get a chill down my spine.

153
00:13:50,989 --> 00:13:52,251
I think about it even now...

154
00:13:53,024 --> 00:14:00,328
The man I truly wished for...
The body I wanted the most... Kimimaro.

155
00:14:01,232 --> 00:14:05,032
And if only he hadn't been stricken
with disease,

156
00:14:05,103 --> 00:14:07,731
the assassination of the Hokage
would've gone smoother.

157
00:14:08,306 --> 00:14:09,671
<i>Seal!</i>

158
00:14:20,718 --> 00:14:21,514
<i>My arms...</i>

159
00:14:22,053 --> 00:14:25,750
<i>Now...you can no longer use</i>
<i>either of your arms...</i>

160
00:14:26,424 --> 00:14:28,858
<i>And since you can't use your arms,</i>

161
00:14:28,927 --> 00:14:30,986
<i>you can't weave Sign...</i>

162
00:14:31,062 --> 00:14:34,190
<i>You no longer possess Ninjutsu!</i>

163
00:14:36,768 --> 00:14:41,068
<i>Your ambition of crushing</i>
<i>the Hidden Leaf...dies right here!</i>

164
00:14:42,874 --> 00:14:45,809
<i>Orochimaru, you fool...</i>

165
00:14:46,344 --> 00:14:51,407
<i>It's unfortunate that we can't leave</i>
<i>together but, my disciple...</i>

166
00:14:52,617 --> 00:14:55,450
<i>Let's meet in the other world</i>
<i>one day...</i>

167
00:15:25,883 --> 00:15:29,341
<i>Sasuke...</i>
<i>Sasuke's not here yet?</i>

168
00:15:33,191 --> 00:15:36,251
We wouldn't have needed to go
through such an experience.

169
00:15:38,196 --> 00:15:44,066
In the world, very often things don't go
as we want them to.

170
00:15:47,972 --> 00:15:52,534
It's only a matter of time,
Lord Orochimaru.

171
00:16:06,090 --> 00:16:10,186
<i>When Tayuya comes back...</i>
<i>I'll kill her.</i>

172
00:16:11,696 --> 00:16:13,095
Hold it.

173
00:16:15,266 --> 00:16:16,255
Hey!

174
00:16:26,778 --> 00:16:29,645
Now then, how shall I defeat you?

175
00:16:45,596 --> 00:16:46,620
You...

176
00:16:47,665 --> 00:16:48,723
<i>Those eyes...</i>

177
00:16:50,301 --> 00:16:53,896
<i>It seems he possesses</i>
<i>a peculiar Chakra.</i>

178
00:16:55,106 --> 00:17:00,271
What does Orochimaru want to do...?
Why's he after Sasuke?

179
00:17:07,952 --> 00:17:11,786
Lord Orochimaru has already
obtained Immortality Jutsu...

180
00:17:12,423 --> 00:17:18,328
A long time is necessary to get every Jutsu
and obtain everything in the world.

181
00:17:18,730 --> 00:17:22,063
What does that have to do
with Sasuke?!

182
00:17:22,533 --> 00:17:27,402
"Immortal" doesn't mean that
the flesh is being maintained as is...

183
00:17:28,306 --> 00:17:30,536
Before his body decays,

184
00:17:30,608 --> 00:17:34,442
a strong and new flesh will be made
into a vessel for his soul.

185
00:17:35,847 --> 00:17:36,939
That's...

186
00:17:37,615 --> 00:17:39,583
Are you saying that's Sasuke?!

187
00:17:41,252 --> 00:17:43,982
Yes... That's right.

188
00:17:45,156 --> 00:17:48,956
I won't let such a thing happen!

189
00:17:50,027 --> 00:17:54,964
Idiot... What will come of sending
one shrimp punk in pursuit?

190
00:17:55,867 --> 00:17:58,927
And looking at things
in terms of time,

191
00:17:59,003 --> 00:18:02,234
up until now you probably sacrificed
one member each time

192
00:18:02,306 --> 00:18:05,241
in order for the group
to move forward.

193
00:18:08,746 --> 00:18:12,182
Is that guy called Sasuke
that important?

194
00:18:12,750 --> 00:18:17,551
How many of your men do you intend
to sacrifice for the sake of just one person?

195
00:18:18,656 --> 00:18:20,123
You incompetent punk.

196
00:18:23,594 --> 00:18:26,062
Heh... Indeed...

197
00:18:27,131 --> 00:18:31,534
For me, this is my first mission
as a platoon leader.

198
00:18:31,769 --> 00:18:36,138
It's very disquieting having
comrades gradually whittled down,

199
00:18:36,207 --> 00:18:40,473
and I didn't know if my own judgments
were correct or not.

200
00:18:43,548 --> 00:18:47,484
As a squad leader with
the lives of the party in my hands...

201
00:18:47,552 --> 00:18:50,282
respecting the lives in
the four-member party,

202
00:18:50,354 --> 00:18:53,983
rather than the life of one person
taken by the enemy...

203
00:18:54,058 --> 00:18:58,893
and deciding to abort a mission
that's too dangerous, would be by the book.

204
00:18:59,330 --> 00:19:01,855
Then, why didn't you do that?

205
00:19:02,166 --> 00:19:06,899
The world doesn't go
by the book very often...

206
00:19:10,575 --> 00:19:13,669
Since not one person in my squad
would do something like

207
00:19:13,744 --> 00:19:21,480
abandon a captured comrade and give up
fighting for the sake of their own safety.

208
00:19:23,120 --> 00:19:24,815
Me included.

209
00:19:28,459 --> 00:19:31,826
Being the cloud-loving loafer myself,

210
00:19:31,896 --> 00:19:35,559
I am not cut out to be a squad leader
who gives orders to comrades.

211
00:19:37,001 --> 00:19:44,237
The only thing I can do for them...
is to have faith in them.

212
00:19:44,909 --> 00:19:48,902
Listen. I'm not thinking anything
like they were sacrifices.

213
00:19:49,080 --> 00:19:51,981
I'm not thinking anything
like they've died.

214
00:19:53,784 --> 00:19:57,220
Don't mock my comrades.

215
00:20:02,460 --> 00:20:03,518
<i>I got you.</i>

216
00:20:07,698 --> 00:20:08,892
Summoning Jutsu!

217
00:20:25,383 --> 00:20:27,783
This doesn't... look so good.

218
00:20:30,187 --> 00:20:32,587
I'll play a melody of death for you.

219
00:20:33,057 --> 00:20:36,493
Don't you mock us,
you damned punk.

220
00:20:49,307 --> 00:20:51,741
I won't let you take Sasuke,
no matter what.

221
00:20:53,077 --> 00:20:53,941
Interesting.

222
00:21:11,796 --> 00:21:14,196
<i>For the first time, I spoke to you</i>

223
00:21:14,265 --> 00:21:17,291
<i>And you smiled</i>

224
00:21:17,535 --> 00:21:19,833
<i>For the first time, I was able to speak</i>

225
00:21:19,904 --> 00:21:22,634
<i>In my own words</i>

226
00:21:22,707 --> 00:21:28,270
<i>Would you think it was</i>
<i>a bother if I approached you?</i>

227
00:21:28,612 --> 00:21:33,811
<i>Despite my doubts,</i>
<i>I worked up my courage</i>

228
00:21:34,085 --> 00:21:39,489
<i>My clumsy attempts with words</i>

229
00:21:39,690 --> 00:21:45,219
<i>You listened without turning away</i>

230
00:21:46,197 --> 00:21:51,396
<i>No wonder I get carried away by you</i>

231
00:21:51,802 --> 00:21:58,469
<i>But you don't feel anything for me, do you?</i>

232
00:21:58,976 --> 00:22:01,672
<i>I feel so sad</i>

233
00:22:01,746 --> 00:22:02,644
<i>But...</i>

234
00:22:02,713 --> 00:22:05,113
<i>For the first time, I spoke to you</i>

235
00:22:05,182 --> 00:22:08,151
<i>And you smiled</i>

236
00:22:08,285 --> 00:22:10,879
<i>For the first time, I was able to speak</i>

237
00:22:10,955 --> 00:22:13,947
<i>In my own words</i>

238
00:22:14,125 --> 00:22:16,457
<i>For the first time, I spoke to you</i>

239
